  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0001",
          "zh": "蒙恬者，其先齊人也。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0002",
          "zh": "恬大父蒙驁，自齊事秦昭王，官至上卿。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0003",
          "zh": "秦莊襄王元年，蒙驁為秦將，伐韓，取成皋、滎陽，作置三川郡。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0004",
          "zh": "二年，蒙驁攻趙，取三十七城。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0005",
          "zh": "始皇三年，蒙驁攻韓，取十三城。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0006",
          "zh": "五年，蒙驁攻魏，取二十城，作置東郡。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0007",
          "zh": "始皇七年，蒙驁卒。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0008",
          "zh": "驁子曰武，武子曰恬。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0009",
          "zh": "恬嘗書獄典文學。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0010",
          "zh": "始皇二十三年，蒙武為秦裨將軍，與王翦攻楚，大破之，殺項燕。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0011",
          "zh": "二十四年，蒙武攻楚，虜楚王。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0012",
          "zh": "蒙恬弟毅。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Meng Tian, his ancestor Qi person. Tian grandfather Meng Ao, from Qi served Qin Zhao Wang, office to upper minister. Qin Zhuangxiang Wang first year, Meng Ao as Qin general, attacked Han, took Chenggao, Xingyang, established three rivers commandery. Second year, Meng Ao attacked Zhao, took thirty seven cities. Shi Huang third year, Meng Ao attacked Han, took thirteen cities. Fifth year, Meng Ao attacked Wei, took twenty cities, established Dong commandery. Shi Huang seventh year, Meng Ao died. Ao son called Wu, Wu son called Tian. Tian once studied prison law literature. Shi Huang twenty-third year, Meng Wu as Qin deputy general, with Wang Jian attacked Chu, greatly broke it, killed Xiang Yan. Twenty-fourth year, Meng Wu attacked Chu, captured Chu king. Meng Tian younger brother Yi.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0013",
          "zh": "始皇二十六年，蒙恬因家世得為秦將，攻齊，大破之，拜為內史。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0014",
          "zh": "秦已并天下，乃使蒙恬將三十萬眾北逐戎狄，收河南。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0015",
          "zh": "筑長城，因地形，用制險塞，起臨洮，至遼東，延袤萬餘里。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0016",
          "zh": "於是渡河，據陽山，逶蛇而北。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0017",
          "zh": "暴師於外十餘年，居上郡。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0018",
          "zh": "是時蒙恬威振匈奴。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0019",
          "zh": "始皇甚尊寵蒙氏，信任賢之。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0020",
          "zh": "而親近蒙毅，位至上卿，出則參乘，入則御前。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0021",
          "zh": "恬任外事而毅常為內謀，名為忠信，故雖諸將相莫敢與之爭焉。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Shi Huang twenty-sixth year, Meng Tian because family background got as Qin general, attacked Qi, greatly broke it, appointed as inner shi. Qin already united world, then made Meng Tian lead thirty thousand crowd north pursue Rong Di, took Henan. Built long wall, according to terrain, used control dangerous passes, rose Lintao, to Liaodong, extended ten thousand plus li. Thus crossed river, occupied Yang mountain, winding snake north. Exposed troops outside ten plus years, dwelt Shang commandery. At time Meng Tian might shook Xiongnu. Shi Huang much honored favored Meng clan, trusted considered worthy them. Yet personally close Meng Yi, position to upper minister, out then accompany chariot, enter then before throne. Tian in charge outer affairs yet Yi constantly as inner plans, named loyal trustworthy, thus though various generals chancellors none dared contend with them.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0022",
          "zh": "趙高者，諸趙疏遠屬也。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0023",
          "zh": "趙高昆弟數人，皆生隱宮，其母被刑僇，世世卑賤。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0024",
          "zh": "秦王聞高彊力，通於獄法，舉以為中車府令。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0025",
          "zh": "高既私事公子胡亥，喻之決獄。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0026",
          "zh": "高有大罪，秦王令蒙毅法治之。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0027",
          "zh": "毅不敢阿法，當高罪死，除其宦籍。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0028",
          "zh": "帝以高之敦於事也，赦之，復其官爵。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Zhao Gao, various Zhao distant branch. Zhao Gao brothers several persons, all born hidden palace, mother suffered punishment executed, generations low base. Qin king heard Gao strong forceful, versed in prison law, raised as middle chariot bureau commander. Gao already privately served crown prince Hu Hai, taught decide cases. Gao had great crime, Qin king commanded Meng Yi govern treat it. Yi dared not bend law, should Gao crime die, removed his eunuch register. Emperor because Gao devoted to affairs, pardoned him, restored his office rank.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0029",
          "zh": "始皇欲游天下，道九原，直抵甘泉，乃使蒙恬通道，自九原抵甘泉，塹山堙谷，千八百里。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0030",
          "zh": "道未就。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Shi Huang wished tour world, road Jiu Yuan, straight reach Gan Quan, then made Meng Tian open road, from Jiu Yuan to Gan Quan, trench mountains fill valleys, thousand eight hundred li. Road not completed.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0031",
          "zh": "始皇三十七年冬，行出游會稽，并海上，北走瑯邪。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0032",
          "zh": "道病，使蒙毅還禱山川，未反。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Shi Huang thirty-seventh year winter, traveled out tour Kuaiji, along sea, north went Langye. Road sick, made Meng Yi return pray mountains rivers, not returned.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0033",
          "zh": "始皇至沙丘崩，祕之，群臣莫知。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0034",
          "zh": "是時丞相李斯、公子胡亥、中車府令趙高常從。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0035",
          "zh": "高雅得幸於胡亥，欲立之，又怨蒙毅法治之而不為己也。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0036",
          "zh": "因有賊心，乃與丞相李斯、公子胡亥陰謀，立胡亥為太子。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0037",
          "zh": "太子已立，遣使者以罪賜公子扶蘇、蒙恬死。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0038",
          "zh": "扶蘇已死，蒙恬疑而復請之。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0039",
          "zh": "使者以蒙恬屬吏，更置。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0040",
          "zh": "胡亥以李斯舍人為護軍。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0041",
          "zh": "使者還報，胡亥已聞扶蘇死，即欲釋蒙恬。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0042",
          "zh": "趙高恐蒙氏復貴而用事，怨之。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Shi Huang reached Shaqiu collapsed, secret it, ministers none knew. At time chancellor Li Si, crown prince Hu Hai, middle chariot bureau commander Zhao Gao constantly followed. Gao usually got favored by Hu Hai, wished establish him, again resented Meng Yi governed treated him not for self. Because had thief heart, then with chancellor Li Si, crown prince Hu Hai secretly plotted, established Hu Hai as crown prince. Crown prince already established, sent envoy with crime granted crown prince Fu Su, Meng Tian die. Fu Su already died, Meng Tian doubted yet again requested it. Envoy with Meng Tian gave officials, changed placed. Hu Hai with Li Si retainer as protect army. Envoy returned reported, Hu Hai already heard Fu Su died, then wished release Meng Tian. Zhao Gao feared Meng clan again noble employ affairs, resented them.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0043",
          "zh": "毅還至，趙高因為胡亥忠計，欲以滅蒙氏，乃言曰：「臣聞先帝欲舉賢立太子久矣，而毅諫曰『不可』。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0044",
          "zh": "若知賢而俞弗立，則是不忠而惑主也。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0045",
          "zh": "以臣愚意，不若誅之。」",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0046",
          "zh": "胡亥聽而系蒙毅於代。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0047",
          "zh": "前已囚蒙恬於陽周。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0048",
          "zh": "喪至咸陽，已葬，太子立為二世皇帝，而趙高親近，日夜毀惡蒙氏，求其罪過，舉劾之。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen",
          "model": "grok-1.5",
          "literal": "Yi returned arrived, Zhao Gao because for Hu Hai loyal planned, wished extinguish Meng clan, then spoke: 'Minister heard previous emperor wished raise worthy establish crown prince long, yet Yi advised 'cannot'. If knew worthy yet deliberately not establish, then not loyal confused lord. With minister foolish intent, not equal execute him.' Hu Hai listened imprisoned Meng Yi at Dai. Before already imprisoned Meng Tian at Yang Zhou. Funeral reached Xianyang, already buried, crown prince established as Second Emperor, yet Zhao Gao close, day night slander hated Meng clan, sought their crimes faults, raised impeached them.",
          "idiomatic": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0049",
          "zh": "子嬰進諫曰：「臣聞故趙王遷殺其良臣李牧而用顏聚，燕王喜陰用荊軻之謀而倍秦之約，齊王建殺其故世忠臣而用后勝之議。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "s0050",
          "zh": "此三君者，皆各以變古者失其國而殃及其身。",
          "translations": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
              "model": "grok-code-fast-1",
              "reviewed": true
            }
